title: Fix bug which caused too many ships in randomly generated boards
message:
Fix bug which caused too many ships in randomly generated boards

generator/Levels.js used a global variable to hold a randomly generated
board. This variable was reused without being cleared inbetween function
calls, resulting in the number of cells occupied by ships doubling for
each function call.

This commit fixes that bug and removes the global state.

title: Make a newly created game include its boards in the JSON response
message:
Make a newly created game include its boards in the JSON response

This is a very ugly solution. Upon creating a game, we need to actually
create the game (which returns a promise), set its boards (which returns
another promise) and respond to the request when both of these promises
have finished. Furthermore, it seems that we need to

  include: [models.Board]

in order for a game's boards to be included in the response, which means
that we also need to do a `models.Game.find()`.

Because the board attributes are set asynchronously, the game which is
returned from `startGame()` does not necessarily (and, in fact, does
not) have its boards set at the time of return, resulting in an empty
array being returned for the `boards` attribute. The only workaround
I've found so far is to perform yet another `find()`, which runs after
the appropriate boards are in place. Whether this is a reliable
solution, or if it's subject to race conditions, I'm not actually sure.
It is, however, both ugly and currently working. So I'm pushing it,
hoping to find a better solution in the future.

title: Make the Board model a Sequelize model
message:
Make the Board model a Sequelize model

This commit does three things:

* changes the existing Board model to a Sequelize model
* adds an initialization file for all models (models/index.js)
* moves the Cell model from its own separate file to models/Board.js,
  and adds serialization / deserialization code for storing the cells
  as a (string) property of a Board rather than creating 100 cell
  records for every game
